Pet --<br>
<br>
don't give up so soon!  Besides ... your archery hireling probably needed to be replaced with one of the caster hirelings in Act III.  Those hirelings can use shields, which means that their defense and resistances are much higher than the archer.  Both the archer and the caster do range attacks -- a lot of people like the fast-casting cold caster (I personally use the fire caster to give my wolves and vines something to chew on).<br>
<br>
I haven't experienced any bugs aside from locking up, but I do keep a daily backup of my character file (you only need the .d2* and .key).  You might want to start doing that to avoid future bugs.<br>
<br>
The v1.09 patch just took away my ability to craft cool items.  *shrug*  I hope they enable or discover the new recipes soon.<br>
<br>
But Diablo has very little time commitment compared to EQ.<br>
<br>
If I read your past posts correctly, you've found the Death's Touch sword.  That's part of a three-piece set.  I happened to be lucky and found the other parts (a glove and a sash) back when I was around level 12.  Another friend found the sword.  It's a fantastic set for a normal-difficulty character!<br>
<br>
